This paper is primarily focused on benchmarking super-resolution algorithms on real data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which could potentially place it in the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of ground truth data and quantitative evaluations also suggests the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the inclusion of motion types and photometric conditions in the dataset could potentially place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
